<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-528-400  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 528 400.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  June 1990 v15 n6 p234(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>On the threshold of a dream. (the progress to hypermedia requiresfiber-optic broadband networks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Solomon, Richard Jay.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The development of hypermedia services (such as advanced videotextinformation services) requires such high-speed communicationstechnologies such as fiber-optic broadband networks.andP;  Hypermediaintegrates online interaction and data base, advanced real-timevideo, audio and computer display technologies.andP;  The transmissionof such data intensive real-time services also requires newcommunications standards, a digital-based open architecturedisplay technology, and advances in artificial intelligence anddata base technology.andP;  Integrated Services Digital Network (ISDN)standard technology provides a step towards the delivery ofhypermedia, but it would be difficult to adequately implement'full-fledged' hypermedia on ISDN.andP;  Broadband ISDN will deliverabout 90 times the throughput of primary-rate ISDN.andP;  The outlookfor broadband ISDN and high-definition television are discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ISDNMultimedia TechnologyBroadbandTrendsIntegrated SystemsDesktop videoOptical communicationsNetworks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>